A buffer is made from equal concentrations of a weak acid and its conjugate base. Doubling the volume of the buffer solution by adding water has what effect on its pH? The pH of a buffer is lowered by 1.5 when it contains 1% water.
Does adding water to a buffer made of acid and a conjugate base lower its PH value or raise it? Adding water to a buffer made of acid and a conjugate base lowers its PH value or raises it.
Does adding water to a buffer made of acid and a conjugate base lower its PH value? Adding water to a buffer made of acid and a conjugate base lowers its PH value.
